# FORE — environment variables (local dev — DO NOT COMMIT .env.local)

## Core (always)

```bash
# ML_MODE=inline  → run math inside Next.js (NO Render needed — recommended for Vercel-only deploy)
# ML_MODE=render  → call external Python service at RENDER_ML_BASE_URL
# Default: inline when RENDER_ML_BASE_URL is unset, external when set
ML_MODE=inline
RENDER_ML_BASE_URL=
GROQ_API_KEY=
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant
GROQ_CRITIC_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# Tier 2 optional APIs (leave blank to disable those features)
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM
EXA_API_KEY=

# Tier 2 feature flags (default true in production demo)
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_SELF_VERIFY=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_BROWSER_STORAGE=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_DARK_MODE=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_LOADING_SKELETONS=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_CHART_ANIMATIONS=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_MULTI_CURRENCY=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_VOICE_INPUT=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_VOICE_NARRATION=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_EXA_GROUNDING=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_EXPORT_AHEAD=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_TRANSPORT_BENCHMARK=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_PERSONA_COMPARE=true
```

## Full-stack mode (FORE Blueprint 2 — JWT + PostgreSQL)

When `DATABASE_URL` is set, auth middleware activates and real bank CSV upload is available.

```bash
# PostgreSQL (Neon, Supabase, Railway, or local)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fore:fore_dev_pass@localhost:5432/fore

# JWT signing secret (long random string, min 32 chars)
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=

# AES-256 key for encrypting transaction descriptions at rest
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
DATA_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
```

### Setup

```bash
npm install
npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push    # or: npx prisma migrate dev
npm run dev
```

Register at `/register`, upload bank CSV on PAST, or use demo personas.

See [docs/SECURITY.md](docs/SECURITY.md) for how real bank data is protected.
